Robox: A graphical Python learning environment

Robox is a grahical environment for python programming that lets people learn programming while having interesting and cool things happen on the screen. Robox is inspired by MicroWorlds

Installation:
    Linux:   Install Python 2.7 and your ditribution's version of pygtk and pygtksourceview 
             Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install python-gtk2 python-gtksourceview2
    
    Windows: Install the Python 2.7 and PyGtk all-in-one installer from
             http://ftp.gnome.org/pub/GNOME/binaries/win32/pygtk/2.24/pygtk-all-in-one-2.24.0.win32-py2.7.msi
             **You must select the GtkSouceView component for installation**
             


Execution:
    run the file robox.py
